org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics.BasicKineticLaw

Packages that use BasicKineticLaw
org.sbml.squeezer This is the core of SBMLsqueezer as it contains the central classes for reaction type analysis, kineticl law generation and some specialized exceptions. 
org.sbml.squeezer.gui This package contains all necessary classes for the graphical user interface. 
org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics This package contains one class for each supported kinetic law.

Subclasses of BasicKineticLaw in org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics
 class AdditiveModelLinear
          This class creates an equation based on a linear additive model.
 class AdditiveModelNonLinear
          This class creates an equation based on a non-linear additive model.
 class CommonSaturable
          This class creates the common saturable rate law according to Liebermeister et al.
 class ConvenienceKinetics
           This is the thermodynamically independent form of the convenience kinetics.
 class DirectSaturable
          This class creates the direct saturable rate law according to Liebermeister et al.
 class ForceDependent
          Force dependent rate law (FD) according to Liebermeister et al 2009.
 class GeneralizedMassAction
          This class creates rate equations according to the generalized mass action rate law.
 class HillEquation
          This class creates a Hill equation as defined in the paper “Hill Kinetics meets P Systems: A Case Study on Gene Regulatory Networks as Computing Agents in silico and in vivo” of Hinze, T.; Hayat, S.; Lenser, T.; Matsumaru, N., and Dittrich, P., 2007.
 class HSystem
          This class creates a non-linear additive equation form Hadeler, K.: “Gedanken zur Parameteridentifikation.” Personal Communication, 2003, and Spieth, C.; Hassis, N.; Streichert, F.; Supper, J.; Beyreuther, K., and Zell, A.
 class IrrevCompetNonCooperativeEnzymes
          Irreversible non-exclusive non-cooperative competitive inihibition, a special case of the KineticLaws defined by SBO term identifier 199, 29, 267, or 273 depending on the structure of the reaction.
 class IrrevNonModulatedNonInteractingEnzymes
          This class implements SBO:0000150 and all of its special cases.
 class MichaelisMenten
          This is the well-known (Henry-) Michaelis-Menten equation and can be found in the SBO under one of the following terms (depending on the specific structure of the underlying Reaction): 28, 199, 266, 269, 275, 276, or 326.
 class MultiplicativeSaturable
          This class creates the mulitiplicative saturable kinetic equation according to Liebermeister et al.
 class NetGeneratorLinear
          This class creates an equation based on an linear additive model as defined in the paper “The NetGenerator Algorithm: Reconstruction of Gene Regulatory Networks” of Töpfer, S.; Guthke, R.; Driesch, D.; Wötzel, D., and Pfaff 2007
 class NetGeneratorNonLinear
          This class creates an equation based on an non-linear additive model as defined in the paper “The NetGenerator Algorithm: Reconstruction of Gene Regulatory Networks” of Töpfer, S.; Guthke, R.; Driesch, D.; Wötzel, D., and Pfaff 2007
 class OrderedMechanism
          Rate law for the bi-uni or bi-bi ordered mechanism.
 class PingPongMechanism
          Kinetic law that describes the ping-pong reaction mechanism.
 class RandomOrderMechanism
          This class creates a kinetic equation according to the random order mechanism (see Cornish-Bowden: Fundamentals of Enzyme Kinetics, p.
 class ReversiblePowerLaw
          Represents the reversible power law (RP) from Liebermeister et al.
 class SpecialHillEquation
          This class creates Hill equation as defined in the PhD thesis “Modeling Non-Linear Dynamic Phenomena in Biochemical Networks” of Nicole Radde and the paper “Modeling Non-Linear Dynamic Phenomena in Biochemical Networks“ of Nicole Radde and Lars Kaderali.
 class SSystem
          This class creates a S-System equation as defined in the papers: Tournier, L.: “Approximation of dynamical systems using S-systems theory: application to biological systems” Spieth, C.; Streichert, F.; Speer, N., and Zell, A.: “Optimizing Topology and Parameters of Gene Regulatory Network Models from Time-Series Experiments” Spieth, C.; Hassis, N.; Streichert, F.; Supper, J.; Beyreuther, K., and Zell, A.: “Comparing Mathematical Models on the Problem of Network Inference” and Hecker, M.; Lambeck, S.; Töpfer, S.; Someren, E.
 class Vohradsky
          This class creates an equation based on an additive model as defined in the papers “Neural network model of gene expression.” of Vohradský, J.
 class Weaver
          This class creates an equation based on an additive model as defined in the paper “Modeling regulatory networks with weight matrices” of Weaver, D.; Workman, C., and Stormo, G.
 class ZerothOrderForwardGMAK
          This class creates generalized mass action rate equations with zeroth order in all reactants.
 class ZerothOrderReverseGMAK
          Mass action rate law for zeroth order reverse reactions.
